<h1>Take Survey</h1>

<%= form_with scope: :surveys, local: true do |form| %>
	<p>
		<%= form.label :name %>&nbsp;
		<%= form.text_field :name %>
	</p>

	<p>
		I will answer as a...<br>
		<%= form.radio_button :type, 'developer', :checked => true %> 
		<%= label :type_developer, 'Developer' %>
		<%= form.radio_button :type, 'user' %>
		<%= label :type_user, 'User' %>
	</p>


<p>
	The following are the definitions of each quality factor as stated in the journal <em>“Customizing ISO 9126 quality model for evaluation of B2B applications”</em> to give a better understanding:<br>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Functionality</strong> - a set of attributes that bear on the existence of a set of functions and their specified properties</li>
	<li><strong>Reliability</strong> - a set of attributes that bear on the capability of software to maintain its level of performance under stated conditions for a stated period of time.</li>
	<li><strong>Usability</strong> - set of attributes that bear on the effort needed for use, and on the individual assessment of such use, by a stated or implied set of users</li>
	<li><strong>Efficiency</strong> - set of attributes that bear on the relationship between the level of performance of the software and the amount of resources used.</li>
	<li><strong>Portability</strong> - set of attributes that bear on the ability of software to be transferred from one environment to another</li>
	<li><strong>Maintainability</strong> - set of attributes that bear on the effort needed to make modifications</li>
</ul>
	In each row of the table below, which quality factor is more important with respect to a UHRIS applications? And how strongly?<br>Please check the table below and rate the factors from 1 to 5. If you believe the second quality is more important than the first quality factor, add a negative to your rating to signify your preference.<br>

	(5 = First Quality Factor is way more important than Second Quality Factor)<br>
	(0 = First Quality Factor is of equal importance with the Second Quality Factor)<br>
	(-5 = Second Quality Factor is way more important than First Quality Factor)
</p>


<table>
	<thead>
		<tr> 
			<th style="border:1px solid black">First Quality Factor</th>
			<th style="border:1px solid black">Second Quality Factor</th>
			<th style="border:1px solid black">Stregth of Preference (-5 to 5)</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Functionality</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Reliability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_FR %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Functionality</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Usability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_FU %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Functionality</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Efficiency</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_FE %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Functionality</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Portability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_FP %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Maintainability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Portability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_MP %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Maintainability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Functionality</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_MF %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Efficiency</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Maintainability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_EM %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Efficiency</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Portability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_EP %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Portability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Usability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_PU %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Portability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Reliability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_PR %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Usability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Efficiency</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_UE %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Usability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Maintainability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_UM %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Reliability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Efficiency</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_RE %></td>
		</tr>

		<tr>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Reliability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black">Usability</td>
			<td style="border:1px solid black"><%= form.text_field :rate_RU %></td>
		</tr>

	</tbody>
</table>

<br>

<%= link_to 'To Thanks', thank_path %>

<%= form.submit %>
<br>

<% end %>







